         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/11/88 ¶  ¶ I should be very sorry, dear Mr Tepper, if my last remarks with regard to the Kangaroo Island ¶  plants led to a disagreement between you and Professor Tate, and I myself must feel his d...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.11.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply 30.11.88'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>28/11/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es sollte mir sehr leid thun, lieber Herr Tepper, wenn meine letzten Bemerkungen hinsichtlich der Käng. Ins. Pflanzen zu einem Zerwürfniss zwischen Ihnen u Hr. Prof. Tate führen, u ich selbst seine Unzufriedenheit fühlen müsste</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Schon im "Census" habe ich angegeben, dass Brachycome überhaupt nur ein subgenus von Bellis sei; selbst Labillardière nannte die <name key="Brachycome%20graminea">Brachycome graminea</name> ursprünglich <name key="Bellis%20graminea">Bellis graminea</name> (1805). Asa Gray, Torrey und Steetz haben über dasselbe Theme schon in den vierziger Jahren des Jahrhunderts Notizen veröffentlicht! Es ist übrigens ein gewisser Unterschied im Receptaculum, den die südlichen Arten von den von der nördl Hemisphere trennt</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Bestens grüssend</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Mir ist die Leopoldina hier nicht zugänglich. Das </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Leihen </hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">des Heftes in welchen über die Wirkung von Euc. in Paralysis geschrieben ist, wird wohl nicht möglich sein. Jedenfalls möchte ich nichts aus dem dortigen </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Garten</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> leihe u dadurch verpflichtet werden.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/11/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should be very sorry, dear Mr Tepper, if my last remarks with regard to the Kangaroo Island<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">SA.</p>
               </note> plants led to a disagreement between you and Professor Tate, and I myself must feel his dissatisfaction.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The preceding surviving letter that mentions Kangaroo Island is M to O. Tepper, 7 July 1888 (in this edition as 88-07-07a); the only surviving letter from Tate after July mentioning Kangaroo Island is R. Tate to M, 16 October 1888. Neither of these letters contains an issue likely to have caused or to reflect a disagreement.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Already in the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg> I have indicated that <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Brachycome</seg> is after all only a subgenus of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bellis</seg>
               <seg style="">;</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B83.03.04, p. 77.</p>
               </note> even Labillardière named <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Brachycome%20graminea">Brachycome graminea</name>
               </seg> originally <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Bellis%20graminea">Bellis graminea</name>
               </seg> (1805).<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Labillardière (1804-6), vol. 2, p. 54.</p>
               </note> Asa Gray, Torrey and Steetz have published notes on the same theme as early as the forties of the century! By the way it is a certain difference in the receptaculum that separates the southern species from those of the Northern Hemisphere.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Best greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leopoldina</seg> is not available to me here. The <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">loan</hi>
               </seg> of the part in which the effect of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
               </seg> in paralysis is written about will probably not be possible.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Merensky (1882).</p>
               </note> In any case I should not like to borrow anything from the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">garden</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M was not on good terms with Richard Schomburgk, Director of the Adelaide Botanic Garden: see, for example, M to O. Tepper, 12 December 1879; M to R. Tate, 10 June 1884 (in this edition as 84-06-10a); M to J. Cockburn, 15 August 1886 (in this edition as 86-08-15a).</p>
               </note> there and be obligated thereby.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bellis%20graminea">Bellis graminea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Brachycome%20graminea">Brachycome graminea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
